Privacy Policy - Discord Tags

Last Updated: [Today's Date]

Introduction

This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, and share your data when using Discord Tags.

By using our service, you agree to the practices described in this policy.

Data Collection

We collect server identifiers, server invites, tag names, and tag icons.

This data is collected directly from the user's input and from Discordâ€™s public API.

Data Usage

The collected data is solely used to provide the tagging service.

We do not sell, share, or distribute the data to third parties without user consent.

Data Storage

Data is securely stored in Supabase databases and is accessible only by authorized personnel.

Data Retention

Data is retained for as long as the tag is active or until the user requests deletion.

User Rights

Users may request the modification or deletion of their data by contacting us.

Changes to this Policy

We may update this Privacy Policy periodically. Continued use of the service constitutes acceptance of the revised policy.
